.TH "mask_apply_and_normalize" 9 "mask_apply_and_normalize" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mask_apply_and_normalize \- applies mask on val and normalize the result
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" mask_apply_and_normalize
.BI "(u32 val "  ","
.BI "u32 mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "val" 12
value
.IP "mask" 12
mask to apply and to normalize with
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The normalization is based on the first set bit in the mask
